	<p>
		<term>Section 3: Structures of polyatomic ions</term>
	</p>

	<p>
		In this section, we’re not going to be adding any new knowledge. Instead, we’ll be tying your new skills to material that you’ve learned previously. Polyatomic ions are ions that consist of multiple atoms that are bound together through covalent bonds. In this section you’ll be determining the structure of polyatomic ions that we’ve previously covered and you’ll be determining which atom(s) in the structure contain the formal charges.
	</p>

